<paragraph blockId="28.[800,1453,1444,1820]" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">
The mimeographed labels of 
<collectionCode box="[1164,1185,1573,1596]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15867" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="Herbarium">K</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[1199,1214,1573,1596]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
, and 
<collectionCode box="[1278,1306,1573,1596]" country="Austria" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15588" name="Naturhistorisches Museum Wien" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="Herbarium">W</collectionCode>
indicate “In regione alpina montis Ak-Dagh” but without any numbers. The note on sheet 
<emphasis box="[1001,1029,1637,1661]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">44</emphasis>
reads “Sous ce nº 44 il y a deux espèces l’échant. fructifère appartient a l’arabis 
<taxonomicName authority="DC" authorityName="DC" box="[1225,1376,1668,1693]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevifolia">brevifolia DC</taxonomicName>
l’autre est probablement une espèce nouvelle”, translated by one of us (
<collectionCode box="[808,849,1733,1757]" country="Sweden" name="University of Gothenburg" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="Herbarium">GB</collectionCode>
) as “Under nº 44 there are two species, the fructiferous sample belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="DC." authorityName="DC." box="[1001,1224,1764,1789]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevifolia">
<emphasis box="[1001,1170,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">Arabis brevifolia</emphasis>
DC.
</taxonomicName>
the other is probably a new species”.
</paragraph>
